// MD dot-path graph→bundle integration program (S4-A tail). A single relational container on a
// Postgres engine whose filter predicate carries an MD dot-path scalar — proving the production
// path: the models root's MdModel resolves the path in the front-half (disconnected/R13, so the
// `month.6` qualified member is a deferred coordinate), and the models root's MdBindings lower it to
// SQL in the bundle. `plan.name.Kaufland.month.6.net` reads the `plan` cubelet (long shape,
// invalidate journaling) at both bound grain columns (customer_name, month_num) — the attribute-name
// qualifiers (`name`, `month`) bind Customer.name / Time.month directly (a bare dimension name binds
// its key instead), pinning the full grain keeps the path scalar (filter-predicate position), and the
// int `6` forces MdPath recognition over a column ref. Disconnected (R13): both members are deferred.

uses world "acme.worlds.dev"

container pick(out kept) target erp_pg {
    src  = load(erp.accounts)
    kept = filter(src, plan.name.Kaufland.month.6.net > 100)
}

pick.kept -> display(md_out)
